item.title: Telco regulator and ombudsman join forces
item.description: Australia's telecommunications regulator and the telecommunications dispute resolution scheme have deepened their relationship in a move they say will provide better outcomes for consumers.

item.title: S Korea reports only two new virus cases
item.description: South Korea is reporting two fresh cases of the new coronavirus as its outbreak continues to slow.

item.title: Academic calls for better disability data
item.description: Having easier access to National Insurance Disability Scheme data has been spruiked as an easy fix to improve the system.

item.title: COVID-19 could undo poverty reduction
item.description: Child mortality rates could start to increase after decades of progress due to the global coronavirus pandemic, World Vision warns.

item.title: WA police probe death of woman in Pilbara
item.description: Police are investigating the death of a woman in Western Australia's Pilbara region.

item.title: AMA in SA hit by $2 million fire
item.description: A suspicious fire started in an underground carpark has caused up to $2 million damage to the Australian Medical Association headquarters in Adelaide.

item.title: US Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg in hospital
item.description: United States Supreme Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg is in hospital with an infection caused by a gallstone, but plans to take part in the court's arguments by telephone.

item.title: Retail spending jumped before lockdown
item.description: Retail spending across Australia jumped 8.5 per cent in March as consumers stockpiled food and office supplies in anticipation of coronavirus lockdown measures.

item.title: Freight link restored between SA and Asia
item.description: More than 30 tonnes of fresh South Australian seafood, meat and other produce is on its way to Asia on the first direct freight service from Adelaide since flights were grounded by the coronavirus pandemic.

item.title: Bubs expands partnership with Coles
item.description: Bubs has signed an agreement with Coles to expand its range of infant formula products at 482 supermarkets from early June.
